<br>
The simple fact is that survivability beats a small damage increase every time.  In exp groups you will get hit every so often.  Its guaranteed.  Those hp can let you tank for an extra round, thats another 2 seconds to get healed, or for the enchanter to remez the add etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
In a perfect 1 mob situation will you take a bunch of damage? Not if you use evade correctly, but when was the last time you we're in a group where something didn't go wrong? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 3:15:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14233.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hp Items</span><hr size=1> Gaav others... you do realize that if 100 str doesnt make a difference then neither does avatar....<br>
